1 Nort heastern State University in Tulsa Broken Arrow, as determined
2 by the Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education.
3 The Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education shall fund
4 Northeastern State University at a level not less than its fiscal
5 year 1998 level, and its Education and General Budget shall be held
6 harmless from reductions in succeeding years.
7 It is the intent of the Legislature that Northeastern State
8 University in Broken Arrow be funded at a level consistent with the
9 average allocation and allotment of the institutions in the regional
10 funding tier as established by the Oklahoma State Regents for Higher
11 Education.
12 Beginning with the 2001 - 2002 academic year, degrees earned at
13 Northeastern State University Branch branch in Tulsa Broken Arrow
14 shall be designated as awarded by the Oklahoma State Regents for
15 Higher Education acting through Northeastern State University.
16 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
17 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
18 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
19 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
20 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
